AIM: 
To write a C program to evaluate the expression using library functions in C 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare variables A, B, C and result as float. 
3. Read the values of A, B, and C from the user. 
4. Use the pow() function from <math.h> to compute A2A^2A2. 
5. Substitute the values into the expression: 
6. Display the result. 
7. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
#include <math.h> 
int main() { 
float A, B, C, result; 
printf("Enter value of A: "); 
scanf("%f", &A); 
printf("Enter value of B: "); 
scanf("%f", &B); 
printf("Enter value of C: "); 
scanf("%f", &C); 
result = A + B + (2 * C) / (3 * A) + pow(A, 2) + (2 * B); 
printf("The value of the expression is: %.2f\n", result); 
return 0; 
}
 

